						<summary>

						<p>On a stone built into the floor of a <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in the Mādhavarāyasvāmin temple.</p>						

						<p>Veṅkaṭapati, 1610 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This damaged inscription is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 15 [32], Sādhāraṇa, Pushya śu. 2, Friday</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1610 A.D., December 7, °41.</hi></p>						

						<p>It seems to record a grant of the incomes to the temple of Mādhavēśvara of Gōraṇṭla for the merit of the king and Chikka-Veṅkaṭappa-nāyaka. The donar's name is lost.</p>						

						</summary>
